  * web: performance/security improvement for handling authorization
    http://ganglia.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/ganglia?view=rev&revision=1588
    +1: carenas
    +0: hawson
    -1: bernardli
    bernardli: PHP would look in the current directory for the file to include,
               therefore, adding the "./" is redundant.  In fact I would propose
               that we get rid of all the "./" for the other include_once()
               calls in web/*.
    hawson: If security is an issue, then check/set the include path with 
            the get_include_path() and set_include_path() functions.  I don't
            see that this would affect performance much.

